      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VICTA SPENCER (3) is mixing form lately, finishing out of the placings last time at this track but was a Grade 6 winner two back at this track. Key player on best and expected to bounce back. BLACK AMETHYST (6) stalked the lead from a middle draw and boxed on well to finish 3 lengths back in second (20.11) at Angle Park in a Grade 5 over 342m. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Well-placed to take this out. BRAX KEEPING (1) was well in the market last time but only managed fifth (30.34), beaten 7 lengths. Finished third the start before. The form out of last race has been strong. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. ZIPPING MIGALOO (7) placed last time (22.66) at this track in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 2 lengths. Has already won out of this draw.",
